<br>
Not true, I was able to quad Spirocs in TD using COF at lvl 48-50 (when I quite).  Just make sure to pull lightfoots and not provens.  Provens have more HP and sometimes resist COF (in my experience).   <p><a href=#><img src=http://members.iquest.net/~jynx25/robe.jpg border=0></a>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uyofallien.showPublicProfile?language=EN>yofallien</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/2/01 4:10:29 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=123.topic&index=6>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: lev 48/49 quadding/quinting what spell?</span><hr size=1> I also kited spirocs in TD during  49/50.  3 Lightfoots and 1 watcher is the ideal kite group.  Enough mana to burn the 3 down using CoF and a conflag to finish off the watcher.  If you get a proven in your pull.  Snare, Root, head back down the beach to camp and clear agro.  Come back and give it another shot. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon2.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uinvectus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Invectus</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/2/01 6:36:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=123.topic&index=7>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.forthill.com/invectus/images/veccy.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: lev 48/49 quadding/quinting what spell?</span><hr size=1> Can you who have quadded the Spirocs at 48 to 50 explain from where and how you pulled the birds?<br>
<br>
I have tried pulling two from the bottom of the ramp and found they were too far apart for BoF to stick on both of them. Even with Jboots on, these things are fast - so this resulted quickly in my demise...<br>
<br>
So I have to assume you are Temp Fluxing 4, grouping and then BoF'ing? With Sow instead of Jboots maybe? Can you recommend a better spot to pull from perhaps?<br>
<br>
