Leader of A'Dileab de Paegen<br>
Tunare Server<br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uaalanonnstarbringer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aalanonn Starbringer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/31/01 9:26:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=123.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: lev 48/49 quadding/quinting what spell?</span><hr size=1>      This may sound borderline insane but i quaded spirocs at 42....got 3 lightfoots and a proven.  Jboots was plenty fast enough for me to outrun them and get them all grouped in a nice tight bundle. Once i got them all snared (3 BoF) i proceeded to CoF them....i killed all 3 lightfoots using CoF leaving the proven with about 1/3rd health.  Had to root and camp the proven as i was oom and had burned my harvest on the lightfoots.  But as far as pulling went i cast my lvl 1 nuke on one and ran it through the other 3.  For the 3 lightfoots i did kill i got 2 blue bbl's for but the kites were a little to risky for me at 43.  Moral of the story is alot of the recommended levels that are posted are the SAFE levels.....if you have some gumption you can pull of kites at alot lower than the recommended levels.<br>
<br>
<br>
Aalanonn Starbringer<br>
Wizard of the 43rd Circle<br>
Lanys Tvyl<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uscylth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Scylth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/3/01 8:59:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=123.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: lev 48/49 quadding/quinting what spell?</span><hr size=1>      I just fihnished going from 48 to 51 on the spirocs.  I quadded only the lightfoots and the watchers at 48, but then through 49 and 50 I quadded whatever was there.  I should say that I had the requisite 200 int but I also had +340 in mana items.  It is ideal to take the two at the bottom of the ramp, and the two in the first hut.  I always stayed levitated by the way (with mouse lock spring locked (hehe)) not only to slow the birds when I wanted to, by running them through the water, but also it gave a quick escape to run out into the water to camp.  At 48, if there were say a proven and a lightfoot at the bottom of the ramp I would pull the proven (the lightfoot would not follow) and solo kill him.  I would do the same thing with a proven and a lightfoot in the first hut.  Once I had nothing but lightfoots or watchers I would quad them.  As far as pulling them, the best way is to run straight up the ramp through the first hut and make a run to the water.  Also why I stayed levitated.  I always had all four follow, no reason to hang around cause they double hit fast and hard and they stun.  Two stuns and I would get on the run with less than a bubble of life left.  Then run them up the coast with your eyes open for any potential adds.  I casted 7 cofs after they were all bound, and then repeated the bof.  It would take about 5 more cofs to finish them.  Sometimes I did have to harvest to finish the last one or two.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ukekenewah.showPublicProfile?language=EN>kekenewah</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/28/01 6:34:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=123.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: lev 48/49 quadding/quinting what spell?</span><hr size=1> I've been quad kiting bloodgill goblins in LOIO from level 48 to level 49 today (woot i finally get to use my ice comet).  I'm using CoF.  To run on top of water with levitate after pulling them to the surface I look straight up when I reach the surface and cast my staff of Tflux on the targetted goblin following me.  When i cast the staff of tflux at the surface I suddenly will &quot;pop&quot; on top of the water and be running at tboot speed while they are still swimming.  This allows me to get some distance before we reach shore.  Then I cast BoF to snare them, then quad kite away.   I'm still learning how to deal with resisters of BoF, and regrouping the snared group and the resister.  WHen a pull goes well it is awesome exp.  Bloodgills have very low HP for their level. <p>Kekenewah Silverbear <BR>
